# API Endpoints for Doctor Appointment Booking System

## Authentication & Security

### AuthController (/api/auth)
- POST   /api/auth/login — Log in and receive a JWT token

### User Registration
- POST   /api/users — Register a new user (open to all)

### Using JWT Token
- For all secured endpoints, add the header:
  - Authorization: Bearer &lt;your_jwt_token&gt;

---

## UserController (/api/users)
- GET    /api/users
- GET    /api/users/{id}
- POST   /api/users
- PUT    /api/users/{id}
- DELETE /api/users/{id}

## PatientController (/api/patients)
- GET    /api/patients
- GET    /api/patients/{id}
- POST   /api/patients
- PUT    /api/patients/{id}
- DELETE /api/patients/{id}

## AppointmentController (/api/appointments)
- GET    /api/appointments
- GET    /api/appointments/{id}
- POST   /api/appointments
- PUT    /api/appointments/{id}
- DELETE /api/appointments/{id}

## RoleController (/api/roles)
